        <item>
          <updateDate>2015-10-08T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Final Farewell Act of 2015 </strong></p> <p>This bill directs the Department of Veterans Affairs to permit the interment or funeral, memorial service, or ceremony of a deceased veteran at a national cemetery during weekends, other than federal holiday weekends, upon the request of the veteran's next-of-kin made for religious or cultural reasons.</p> <p> Any grant to assist a state in establishing a veterans' cemetery shall require that the cemetery permits the interment or funeral, memorial service, or ceremony of a deceased veteran during weekends, other than federal holiday weekends, upon the request of the veteran's next-of-kin made for religious or cultural reasons.</p>]]></text>
          <versionCode>00</versionCode>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2015-10-19T18:38:09Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
          <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
          <actionDate>2015-10-08</actionDate>
        </item>
        <item>
          <updateDate>2016-05-23T14:00:01Z</updateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Final Farewell Act of 2016 </strong></p> <p>(Sec. 2) This bill directs the Department of Veterans Affairs to permit the interment or funeral, memorial service, or ceremony of a deceased veteran at a national cemetery during weekends, other than federal holiday weekends, upon the request of the veteran's next-of-kin. </p> <p> Any grant to assist a state in establishing a veterans' cemetery shall require that the cemetery permits the interment or funeral, memorial service, or ceremony of a deceased veteran during weekends, other than federal holiday weekends, upon the request of the veteran's next-of-kin.</p>]]></text>
